Alcheon of Prexus</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukhirgoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>khirgoth</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12/12/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1:39:54 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: /sigh</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I agree with the concept that our ability to lay down AE's puts us in a different class as far as damage output.  (Note I am not addressing multikiting here).  When used with an enchanter who is laying down AE stuns and a cleric that is on the ball, you can put out 500 pts to every mob every 6 (approx.) seconds until you hit 56 where you can chain cast the two PB AE spells we get.  Now you may argue that the ability to lay down damage should not be based on a situation based on a specific set of parameters but wizards are difficult to tune.  Because of our ability to dish out damage FASTER than any other class (Except for possibly a rogue with ragebringer backstabbing/evading), if they greatly increase our damage capacity they upset the balance in PVP as well as make it possible for us to kite bigger mobs when soloing.<br>
<br>
I am pretty much satisfied with my ability to dish out damage (Though the upgraded resists in Hate really suck)  I feel the place where wizards need to be tuned is in the area of mana regen.  I think the issue that wizards that are making the 'I don't dish out as much damage as other classes arguement' is more from, if you are consistently pulling, the melee classes can keep dishing out damage non-stop and with a stamina refresh and heals can keep it up non-stop.  There have been great improvements in the abilities of the melee class to increase this damage rate and though they have not overtaken wizards, they are approaching them.  The difference is when we run out of mana we have to go sit down.  We don't offer any defensive benefits other than evac and we can't buff other classes so our role is limited.<br>
<br>
I will NOT say my wizard sucks.  In fact, he rocks.  If I get bored with a place, I get up and port.  (Ok this has nothing to do with dishing out damage but it definitely fits my play style)  I can solo kite blues, and multikite blues though keeping in the same local area to land AE's can be an adventure.  But I will say we need to be tuned.  Not a major change mind you, but Verant needs to recognize that EQ has very much evolved and that wizards have been ignored to a degree in this evolution.  We need more ways of increasing our mana regen rate.  I have a few suggestions:<br>
<br>
1.  Harvest should have a higher regen curve as you go up in level.<br>
2.  BoF (Our Epic effect)  Should have a higher mana regen.  Though I still disagree that this should be our epic effect at all.<br>
3.  When we get hit with skin spells on, half of the damage should be returned in mana.  (This might be open to abuse, just came to me and haven't considered the ramifications.)<br>
4.  (Ok this one is a little out there) Our epic affect could possibly be a spell that when cast increases our damage output by 50% for 30 seconds and has a regen time of 5 minutes but is only effective on NPC's.<br>
<br>
The first three would increase our ability to inflict damage over a period of several pulls and not impact our ability to inflict damage on a single pull.<br>
<br>
I personally am old school AD&amp;D and would love to see a find familiar (Weak pet with interesting effects) aspect added.<br>
<br>
Now do I think any of these will get implemented.  Well one can only hope.  I think Verant is not in touch with players and balance issues and it seems to me they even have difficulty communicating between project teams (Epic quests/weapons being a huge example).  There would definitely have to be a shift in Verant focus to address a ton of issues that we are seeing as players and I think the main problem is, Verant won't make that shift till the next new MMORPG comes out and sucks out a significant portion of their player base.<br>
<br>
As for now I will continue to play my wizard.  While these issues are frustrating, it is not bad enough for me to give up or flame someone for saying we suck (which I disagree with) or flame someone for saying we are great, we need no changes (Which I would definitely disagree with).<br>
<br>
My 2 cp<br>
<br>
